section2.code:
float cr = sin(angle);
float cb = cos(angle);
float factor;
if (abs(cr) > abs(cb)) {
  factor = 0.5 / abs(cr);
} else {
  factor = 0.5 / abs(cb);
}
cb = cb * factor;
cr = cr * factor;

ol.li:
Calculate r, g and b according to BT.601:float r = 2*(1 - KR)*cr + y;
float b = 2*(1 - KB)*cb + y;
float g = (y - KR*r - KB*b)/KG;

Invert the background color by subtracting the individual channels from 1 each:

rb = 1-rb;
gb = 1-gb;
bb = 1-bb;

Mix the inverted background with the color to adapt, using a mixing factor of 0.2:

rc = 0.2*rb + 0.8*ri;
gc = 0.2*gb + 0.8*gi;
bc = 0.2*bb + 0.8*bi;

section2.code:
y = KR*r + (1 - KR - KB)*g + KB*b;
cb = (b - y) / (1 - KB) / 2
cr = (r - y) / (1 - KR) / 2
